Eight fire engines and 60 crew members at the scene of the blaze - River Gardens Walk, located next to the Thames. Accompanying footage posted on Twitter, Ricky Dukes, an artistic director, said: “Another fire in #Greenwich this morning, along river near Enderby Wharf. Hope everyone is out of the building and safe. Fire brigade is now on the scene.” In a statement, London Fire Brigade confirmed the situation is now under control. The force wrote: "Part of a balcony and a flat on the 10th floor were alight. There are no reports of any injuries at this stage. "The Brigade was called at 8.05amand the fire was under control by 9.13am. Fire crews from Deptford, New Cross, Poplar, Peckham and surrounding stations were at the scene. "The cause of the fire is under investigation."  